%define name @PACKAGE@
%define ver @VERSION@
%define rel 1
%define prefix %{_usr}
%define docdir %{_defaultdocdir}
Summary: GNOME 2.0 Internet Radio Locator program
Name: %{name}
Version: %{ver}
Release: %{rel}
License: GPL
Vendor: ping.uio.no
Packager: Ole Aamot <oka@oka.no>
URL: http://www.ping.uio.no/~oka/src/girl/
Group: Applications/Internet
Source: http://www.ping.uio.no/~oka/src/girl/@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@.tar.gz
BuildRoot: %{_tmppath}/%{name}-root
Requires: gtk2 libgnome libxml2 gnome-vfs2 libgnomeui totem
BuildRequires: /usr/bin/gcc gtk2-devel libgnome-devel libxml2-devel gnome-vfs2-devel libgnomeui-devel
Provides: girl

%description
Girl is a GNOME Internet Radio Locator program that allow users
to easily find live radio programs and audio broadcasted on the
Internet.

Girl is developed on the new GNOME 2.0 platform and it requires
at least one audio helper to be installed.

Enjoy Internet Radio.

